I would remark on the on the Catholic Church and the food kitchen if I could, unfortunately I am a sort-of Lutheran and only ever volunteered at random houses after Hurricane Harvey and a few Libraries, but I do get a good feeling as to how they work from the story, mainly dealing with the mix of different kinds of downtrodden in the soup kitchen. Overall since the setting is "Not New York" it feels like a real city, but I have no idea how the big Northern Cities feel or operate.
